, MO]]\n|event    = [[Backlash (2002)|Backlash]]\n|notes    = After the WWF was renamed World Wrestling Entertainment (WWE) due to a lawsuit by the [[World Wide Fund for Nature]] on May 6, 2002, the title was also renamed: Undisputed WWE Championship and then WWE Undisputed Championship.\n|ref      = <ref name=\"Hogan6\">{{cite web|url=http://www.wwe.com/inside/titlehistory/wwechampionship/30445414114 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20050624014455/http://www.wwe.com/inside/titlehistory/wwechampionship/30445414114 |url-status=dead |archive-date=2005-06-24 |title=Hulk Hogan's sixth reign |publisher=WWE |accessdate=2007-03-22 }}</ref>\n}}{{PWtitlereign\n|sort number = 0.5\n|type = promotion\n|name = [[World Wrestling Entertainment]] (WWE)\n}}{{PWtitlereign\n|number   = 66\n|champion = {{sortname|The|Undertaker}}\n|reign    = 4\n|date     = {{dts|May 19, 2002}}\n|days     = {{age in days nts|May 19, 2002|July 21, 2002}}\n|days2    = yes\n|location = [[Nashville, Tennessee|Nashville, TN]]\n|event    = [[Judgment Day (2002)|Judgment Day]]\n|notes    = \n|ref      = <ref name=\"Undertaker4\">{{cite web|url=http://www.wwe.com/inside/titlehistory/wwechampionship/304454140212 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20050724013906/http://www.wwe.com/inside/titlehistory/wwechampionship/304454140212 |url-status=dead |archive-date=2005-07-24 |title=The Undertaker's fourth reign |publisher=WWE |accessdate=2007-03-22 }}</ref>\n}}{{PWtitlereign\n|number   = 67\n|champion = {{sortname|The|Rock|Dwayne Johnson}}\n|reign    = 7\n|date     = {{dts|July 21, 2002}}\n|days     = {{age in days nts|July 21, 2002|August 25, 2002}}\n|days2    = yes\n|location = [[Detroit|Detroit, MI]]\n|event    = [[Vengeance (2002)|Vengeance]]\n|notes    = This was a [[Professional wrestling match types#Basic non-elimination matches|triple threat match]] also involving [[Kurt Angle]].\n|ref      = <ref name=\"Rock7\">{{cite web|url=http://www.wwe.com/inside/titlehistory/wwechampionship/304454141122 |