ouse of Kara\u0111or\u0111evi\u0107]]\n*[[List of Serbian monarchs]]\n\n==Notes==\n{{reflist|30em}}\n\n==References==\n{{refbegin|40em}}\n* {{cite journal\n  | last = Batakovi\u0107\n  | first = Du\u0161an T.\n  | year = 2002\n  | title = Belgrade in the Nineteenth Century: A Historical Survey\n  | volume = 16\n  | number = 2\n  | journal = Journal of the North American Society for Serbian Studies\n  | publisher = Slavica Publishers\n  | location = Bloomington, Indiana\n  | issn = 0742-3330\n  | url = http://www.serbianstudies.org/publications/pdf/SS_Vol%2016_2002_No%202.pdf\n  | pages = 335\u2013359\n  | ref = harv\n  }}\n* {{cite book\n  | last = Bjelajac\n  | first = Mile\n  | editor1-last = Radan\n  | editor1-first = Peter \n  | editor2-last = Pavkovi\u0107\n  | editor2-first = Aleksandar\n  | year = 1997\n  | title = The Serbs and Their Leaders in the Twentieth Century\n  | chapter = King Petar I Kara\u0111or\u0111evi\u0107\n  | publisher = Ashgate\n  | location = Farnham, England\n  | isbn = 978-1-8552-189-1-8\n  | ref = harv\n  }}\n* {{cite book\n  | last = Dedijer\n  | first = Vladimir\n  | authorlink = Vladimir Dedijer\n  | year = 1966\n  | title = The Road to Sarajevo\n  | publisher = Simon & Schuster\n  | location = New York\n  | oclc = 400010\n  | ref = harv\n  }}\n* {{cite book\n  | last = Judah\n  | first = Tim\n  | authorlink = Tim Judah\n  | year = 2000\n  | origyear = 1997\n  | edition = 2nd\n  | title = The Serbs: History, Myth and the Destruction of Yugoslavia\n  | publisher = Yale University Press\n  | location = New Haven, Connecticut\n  | isbn = 978-0-300-08507-5\n  | url = https://books.google.com/books?id=B4YbP0fPcMYC\n  | ref = harv\n  }}\n* {{cite book\n  | last = Lampe\n  | first = John R.\n  | authorlink = John R. Lampe\n  | year = 2000\n  | origyear = 1996\n  | edition = 2nd\n  | title = Yugoslavia as History: Twice There Was a Country\n  | publisher = Cambridge University Press\n  | location = Cambridge\n  | isbn = 978-0-521-77401-7\n  