nd}}\n\n==External links==\n{{Commons category|Peter I of Serbia}}\n*[http://www.royal.rs The Serbian Royal Family]\n*[http://www.oplenac.rs/wpeng/#sthash.aDfKTmit.dpbs Royal Mausoleum Oplenac]\n*[https://web.archive.org/web/20091229101222/http://www.royalfamily.org/press/press-det/stogodisnjicaeng.pdf Royal Family]\n* {{PM20|FID=pe/013473}}\n\n{{s-start}}\n{{s-hou|[[House of Kara\u0111or\u0111evi\u0107]]|29 June|1844|16 August|1921}}\n{{s-reg}}\n{{s-bef|before=[[Alexander I of Serbia]]}}\n{{s-ttl|title=[[List of Serbian monarchs|King of Serbia]]|years=15 June 1903&nbsp;\u2013 1 December 1918}}\n{{s-non|reason=Expansion of state|reason2=proclaimed King of the Serbs, Croats and Slovenes}}\n{{s-new}}\n{{s-ttl|title=[[List of heads of state of Yugoslavia|King of the Serbs, Croats and Slovenes]]|years=1 December 1918&nbsp;\u2013 16 August 1921}}\n{{s-aft|after=[[Alexander I of Yugoslavia]]}}\n{{s-end}}\n\n{{Serbian monarchs}}\n{{Yugoslav Head of State}}\n{{House of Karageorgevitch}}\n{{Serbian princes}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Peter 01 Of The Serbs, Croats And Slovenes}}\n[[Category:20th-century Serbian monarchs]]\n[[Category:Kings of Yugoslavia]]\n[[Category:Kings of Serbia]]\n[[Category:Serbian princes]]\n[[Category:Serbian translators]]\n[[Category:Yugoslav royalty]]\n[[Category:Eastern Orthodox monarchs]]\n[[Category:Kara\u0111or\u0111evi\u0107 dynasty]]\n[[Category:Recipients of the Order of St. Andrew]]\n[[Category:Grand Crosses of the Order of the Tower and Sword]]\n[[Category:\u00c9cole Sp\u00e9ciale Militaire de Saint-Cyr alumni]]\n[[Category:1844 births]]\n[[Category:1921 deaths]]\n[[Category:People from Belgrade]]\n[[Category:Officers of the French Foreign Legion]]\n[[Category:Burials at the Mausoleum of the Royal House of Kara\u0111or\u0111evi\u0107, Oplenac]]\n[[Category:Serbian Freemasons]] <!--source: http://www.lodge.rs/en/known_masons/ -->\n", "name_user": "HzgiUU149377", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eHonours", "url_page": "